{
  "texts": [
    "An overview is given in Table 10.",
    "Many systems employ external frameworks to leverage Natural Language Understanding (NLU) for interpreting user input.",
    "By using pretrained NLU components, there is no need for training or dataset collection.",
    "Instead, it only requires defining intents and subsequent actions, thereby saving both time and manual effort.",
    "For instance, the system by Sokol and Flach (2018) uses Google's DIY AI Voice Kit 4 to interpret the user question and transform it into a counterfactual statement that can be queried."
  ]
}